Refactor (Level 1, Stage B part 1): split routes.ts — _shared + core mounter

Behavior-preserving; verified tsc + smoke (18/18) + a route-registration diff
(234/234 endpoints register identically, before vs after the split).

- gateway/src/api/routes/_shared.ts: hoist safePath out of routes.ts so the
  per-feature mounters can import it (one-way dep: routes.ts -> mounters).
- gateway/src/api/routes/core.routes.ts (mountCore): health/liveness/readiness
  probes, status dashboard, chat API, project listing, cost, audit, activity
  feed + SSE. Handler bodies moved verbatim.
- routes.ts: import safePath from _shared; replace the inline core section with
  mountCore(app, gateway, baseDir).

Verification harness for the rest of Stage B: enumerate every app.METHOD('path')
across routes.ts + routes/*.ts and diff vs the pre-split baseline. This guards
against the main risk — a dropped/renamed route from a transcription slip — since
gateway is `any`-typed and tsc can't catch service/method typos in handler bodies.

Remaining mounters: memory; settings (vault/config/telegram); projects (+ its
local helpers buildStepUserMessage/getSmartExcerpt/stepNeedsFullManuscript);
documents; personas; media (research/image/tts); ops (lessons/prefs/orchestrator);
export; wave2/3; knowledge; website. The 3 cross-cutting helpers (upload,
gatherChapters, addWaveDisclaimer) get lifted into _shared.ts as param-taking
functions. Final gate before PR: rebuild on Mercury + full tests/openrouter-pipeline.sh.
